Introduction

Base URL: http://localhost:8000

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

POST api/coinbase/webhook

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/coinbase/webhook" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/coinbase/webhook"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Basic Settings Data Fetch

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/basic/settings" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/basic/settings"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

GET api/v1/app-settings

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/app-settings" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/app-settings"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/user/profile/update" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "firstname=rfobdlb"\
    --form "lastname=zlbzhtqxclnxozxjojb"\
    --form "country=edahvzyshyyzapo"\
    --form "phone_code=nogh"\
    --form "phone=d"\
    --form "state=mrucphcxlqegqdvrputqkc"\
    --form "city=dptutbtxoqsy"\
    --form "zip_code=llzkdty"\
    --form "address=czxpyxditjsfaxd"\
    --form "image=@/tmp/php5at9to" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/user/profile/update"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('firstname', 'rfobdlb');
body.append('lastname', 'zlbzhtqxclnxozxjojb');
body.append('country', 'edahvzyshyyzapo');
body.append('phone_code', 'nogh');
body.append('phone', 'd');
body.append('state', 'mrucphcxlqegqdvrputqkc');
body.append('city', 'dptutbtxoqsy');
body.append('zip_code', 'llzkdty');
body.append('address', 'czxpyxditjsfaxd');
body.append('image', document.querySelector('input[name="image"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

    --form "role=incidunt"\
    --form "who_will_pay_options=incidunt"\

    --form "escrow_currency=temporibus"\
    --form "remarks=quibusdam"\
    --form "file[]=@/tmp/php9cSAVL"

    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/user/my-escrow/submit"
);

};

body.append('title', 'cum');
body.append('escrow_category', '20');
body.append('role', 'incidunt');
body.append('who_will_pay_options', 'incidunt');
body.append('buyer_seller_identify', 'voluptatem');
body.append('amount', '31860756.14');
body.append('escrow_currency', 'temporibus');
body.append('remarks', 'quibusdam');
body.append('file[]', document.querySelector('input[name="file[]"]').files[0]);

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/v1/user/api-escrow-action/message/send

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/user/api-escrow-action/message/send" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"escrow_id\": 9995.296,
    \"message\": \"lq\",
    \"files\": [
        \"nwppdpxaubneixtx\"
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/user/api-escrow-action/message/send"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "escrow_id": 9995.296,
    "message": "lq",
    "files": [
        "nwppdpxaubneixtx"
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
